'''Whole Azerbaijan''' ({{lang-az|Bütöv Azərbaycan}}) is an [[irredentism|irredentist]] [[concept]] of uniting [[Azerbaijani people|Azerbaijani]]-inhabited territories into [[Azerbaijan]].
== History == The idea of "Whole Azerbaijan" was formulated by [[Piruz Dilanchi]] in 1991 and defined in 1992 by [[Republic of Azerbaijan|Azerbaijani]] president [[Abulfaz Elchibey]] (s. 1992-93). In 1991, Dilanchi founded the SANLM nationalist organization and in 1997 Elchibey founded the "Whole Azerbaijan Union" (Bütöv Azərbaycan Birliyi) organization.<ref>{{cite web |first=Arif |last=Keskin |url=http://www.turksam.org/tr/a192.html |title=Güney Azerbaycan Milli Demokratik Hareketi Yol Ayrımında |website=TÜRKSAM |date=February 6, 2003 |language=AZ |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120228235923/http://www.turksam.org/tr/a192.html |archivedate=February 28, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://sanlm.org/meramname.php|title=Program of South Azerbaijan National Liberation Movement|website=SANLM|deadurl=yes|archivedate=March 6, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306201707/http://sanlm.org/meramname.php}}</ref> Elchibey published his book on the idea, ''Bütöv Azərbaycan yolunda'', in Turkey in 1998. It argued that the borders of Azerbaijan should extend from [[Derbent]] to the [[Persian Gulf]].<ref name="asam.org.tr">{{cite web|url=http://www.asam.org.tr/tr/yazidosyagoster.asp?ID=1029|title=Satranç Tahtasında Azerbaycan ve Farsistan|first=Arif|last=Rehmoğlu|work=Avrasya Dosyası, Avrasya Stratejik Araştırmalar Merkezi|location=Ankara}}{{dead link|date=November 2017|fix-attempted=yes}}</ref>{{dubious|date=February 2012}} Elchibey argued that this was a territory of Azerbaijani historical ethnic presence.<ref>"Böyük Azərbaycan tarixən şimalda Dərbənddən başlayıb, Həmədan mərkəz olmaqla Bəsrə körfəzinədək uzanırdı" ''Bütöv Azərbaycan yolunda'', Əbülfəz Elchibey, Ecdad Yayınları, Ankara, 1998</ref>{{vs|date=November 2017}} He proposed that Azerbaijan had right to rule it, under a proposed system of governance called "United Azerbaijani Lands" (Birləşmiş Azərbaycan Yurdları).<ref name="asam.org.tr"/> After his death in 2002, it was published postmortem. He opposed the idea of a separate and independent [[Azerbaijan (Iran)|Iranian Azerbaijan]].<ref>''Bütöv Azərbaycan Haqqında'', Yeni Müsavat newspaper, [[Baku]], 2002</ref>{{dubious|date=February 2012}}{{vs|date=November 2017}} [[File:Azeri_language.png|thumb|250px|Distribution of the Azerbaijani language.]]
== Political initiatives == The term Whole Azerbaijan continued in political initiatives including the SANLM (CAMAH) and [[Whole Azerbaijan Popular Front Party]].{{citation needed|date=February 2012}}
== Boundaries == Although the boundaries of Whole Azerbaijan are not strictly defined, some proponents portray them as encompassing the following areas<ref>[http://batu.azeriblog.com/2008/06/08/btvazbycn Bütöv Azərbaycan Haritası]{{deadlink|date=November 2017|fix-attempted=yes}}</ref>{{dubious|date=February 2012}}
*'''[[Azerbaijan (Iran)|Iranian Azerbaijan]]''' - {{flagicon|Iran}} the provinces of [[East Azerbaijan Province|East Azerbaijan]], [[West Azerbaijan Province|West Azerbaijan]], [[Ardabil Province|Ardabil]], and [[Zanjan Province|Zanjan]] *'''[[Western Azerbaijan (political concept)|«Western Azerbaijan»]]''' (''Qərbi Azərbaycan'') - {{flagicon|Armenia}} all the territory of the [[Republic of Armenia]] *'''[[Derbentsky District|Derbent]]''' (''Dərbənd'') - {{flagicon|Russia}} [[Derbentsky District|Derbent district]], [[Republic of Dagestan]] *'''[[Borchali]]''' (''Borçalı'') - {{flagicon|Georgia}} Part of the [[Kvemo Kartli]] province of [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]] *'''[[Iğdır Province]]'''{{citation needed|date=February 2018}} - {{flagicon|Turkey}} [[Eastern Anatolia Region]], [[Turkey]]
